First Department,

March, 1940.

(March 1, 1940.) Charles Emerson Gurley, Respondent, v. Joseph L. Rosenberg, Appellant, Impleaded with Others, Defendants.

Order, so far as appealed from, unanimously affirmed, with twenty dollars costs and disbursements, with leave to defendant-appellant to answer within ten days after service of order on payment of said costs. No opinion. Present • — ■ Martin, P. J., Townley, Dore, Cohn and Callahan, JJ.
